[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    243[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Add a paragraph to the Stage 6 walkthrough or to "Why These Services": "The exposure aggregate read is in the hot path. For a 200-candidate search, the batched DynamoDB read costs roughly 30-80ms at p95. Cache aggressively at the search-orchestrator Lambda (per-container LRU keyed on [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mprovider_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, TTL of 60-120 seconds since the cap is 24-hour-windowed) so warm Lambda containers don't re-read the same providers repeatedly. For very high traffic, consider an in-memory cache (ElastiCache for Redis) fronted by the orchestrator; the consistency window is forgiving (the cap is fairness, not correctness, so a 1-2 minute lag in the count is acceptable)."[K
